nput-wrap"> <input type="text" id="search-input" class="search-input" tabindex="0" placeholder="Search effect-libs" aria-label="Search effect-libs" autocomplete="off"> <label for="search-input" class="search-label"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="search-icon"><use xlink:href="#svg-search"></use></svg></label> </div> <div id="search-results" class="search-results"></div> </div> <nav aria-label="Auxiliary" class="aux-nav"> <ul class="aux-nav-list"> <li class="aux-nav-list-item"> <a href="https://github.com/parischap/effect-libs" class="site-button" > GitHub </a> </li> </ul> </nav> </div> <div id="main-content-wrap" class="main-content-wrap"> <div id="main-content" class="main-content" role="main"> <h{"0": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Array overview", "content": "Extensions to the Effect Array module providing predicates, indexed search, cardinality matching, indexed (un)grouping, sorted-iterator merging/difference, and cycle-aware unfolding. ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#array-overview", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#array-overview" },"1": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Mental model", "content": ". | Type&lt;A&gt; is just ReadonlyArray&lt;A&gt;; functions never mutate the input. | All functions are curried, data-last — call as MArray.fn(arg)(self) or pipe(self, MArray.fn(arg)). They are not data-first/data-last dual. | Equality-based functions (e.g. {@link hasDuplicates}, {@link longestCommonSubArray}, {@link differenceSorted}) compare with Equal.equals. The *With variants take an explicit Equivalence. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mental-model", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mental-model" },"2": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Common tasks", "content": ". | Predicates: {@link hasLength}, {@link hasDuplicates}, {@link hasDuplicatesWith} | Search: {@link findAll}, {@link extractFirst}, {@link getFromEnd}, {@link longestCommonSubArray} | Pattern match: {@link match012} | Unsafe access: {@link unsafeGet}, {@link unsafeGetter} | Modify by position: {@link modifyHead}, {@link modifyInit}, {@link modifyTail}, {@link modifyLast} | Group / ungroup: {@link ungroup}, {@link groupByNum}, {@link groupBy} | Split: {@link splitAtFromRight}, {@link splitNonEmptyAtFromRight} | Map / reduce with short-circuit: {@link mapUnlessNone}, {@link mapUnlessLeft}, {@link reduceUnlessNone}, {@link reduceUnlessLeft} | Sorted operations: {@link mergeSorted}, {@link differenceSorted} | Construct: {@link unfold}, {@link unfoldNonEmpty}, {@link pad} | Format: {@link removeEmptyAndJoin} | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#common-tasks", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#common-tasks" },"3": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Quickstart", "content": "Example (Common predicates and indexed search) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" import * as MPredicate from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MPredicate\" console.log(MArray.hasDuplicates([1, 2, 2, 3])) // true console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3, 2], MArray.findAll(MPredicate.strictEquals(2)))) // [1, 3] . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#quickstart", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#quickstart" },"4": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constructors . | unfold | unfoldNonEmpty | . | Destructors . | getter | mapUnlessLeft | mapUnlessNone | reduceUnlessLeft | reduceUnlessNone | unsafeGetter | . | Models . | Type (interface) | . | Predicates . | hasDuplicates | hasDuplicatesWith | hasLength | . | Utility types . | With (type alias) | . | Utils . | differenceSorted | extractFirst | findAll | getFromEnd | groupBy | groupByNum | longestCommonSubArray | match012 | mergeSorted | modifyHead | modifyInit | modifyLast | modifyTail | pad | removeEmptyAndJoin | splitAtFromRight | splitNonEmptyAtFromRight | takeBut | takeRightBut | ungroup | unsafeGet | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html" },"5": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#constructors" },"6": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "unfold", "content": "Curried version of Array.unfold with optional cycle detection. | Without seedEquivalence, behaves like a curried Array.unfold: keep generating until f returns Option.none. | With seedEquivalence, every seed is recorded; if the same seed reappears, cycleSource is a some of the A produced the first time that seed was processed, allowing the caller to break the cycle. | . Example (Unfold without cycle detection) . import { Option, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const result = pipe( 0, MArray.unfold((n) =&gt; (n &lt; 3 ? Option.some([n, n + 1] as const) : Option.none())) ) console.log(result) // [0, 1, 2] . Signature . export declare const unfold: { &lt;S, A&gt;(f: (s: S) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;MTypes.Pair&lt;A, S&gt;&gt;): (s: S) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; &lt;S, A&gt;( f: (s: S, cycleSource: Option.Option&lt;NoInfer&lt;A&gt;&gt;) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;MTypes.Pair&lt;A, S&gt;&gt;, seedEquivalence: Equivalence.Equivalence&lt;S&gt; ): (s: S) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; } . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unfold", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unfold" },"7": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "unfoldNonEmpty", "content": "Variant of {@link unfold} where each step always produces an A and optionally a next seed S, guaranteeing a non-empty result. | Use when at least one element must be produced. | Cycle detection works the same way as in {@link unfold}. | . Example (Unfold a non-empty array) . import { Option, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const result = pipe( 0, MArray.unfoldNonEmpty((n) =&gt; [n, n &lt; 2 ? Option.some(n + 1) : Option.none()] as const) ) console.log(result) // [0, 1, 2] . Signature . export declare const unfoldNonEmpty: { &lt;S, A&gt;(f: (s: S) =&gt; MTypes.Pair&lt;A, Option.Option&lt;S&gt;&gt;): (s: S) =&gt; MTypes.OverOne&lt;A&gt; &lt;S, A&gt;( f: (s: S, cycleSource: Option.Option&lt;NoInfer&lt;A&gt;&gt;) =&gt; MTypes.Pair&lt;A, Option.Option&lt;S&gt;&gt;, seedEquivalence: Equivalence.Equivalence&lt;S&gt; ): (s: S) =&gt; MTypes.OverOne&lt;A&gt; } . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unfoldnonempty", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unfoldnonempty" },"8": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Destructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#destructors", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#destructors" },"9": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "getter", "content": "Returns a function that retrieves the element at a given index from self, wrapped in an Option. | Use to precompute a getter once when the same array will be queried many times. | The returned function is curried for the index and returns Option.none for out-of-bounds accesses. | . Example (Reusable safe getter) . import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const get = MArray.getter([1, 2, 3]) console.log(get(0)) // Some(1) console.log(get(5)) // None . Signature . export declare const getter: &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;number, Option.Option&lt;A&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#getter", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#getter" },"10": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "mapUnlessLeft", "content": "Maps every element of self with f, returning Result.success of the mapped array if every call succeeds, or the first failure encountered. | Use when each step can produce a typed error. | Short-circuits on the first failure returned by f. | . Example (Map with error handling) . import { Result, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const parseIntSafe = (s: string) =&gt; { const n = parseInt(s) return Number.isNaN(n) ? Result.fail(`Invalid number: ${s}`) : Result.succeed(n) } console.log(pipe([\"1\", \"2\", \"3\"], MArray.mapUnlessLeft(parseIntSafe))) // Success([1, 2, 3]) console.log(pipe([\"1\", \"x\", \"3\"], MArray.mapUnlessLeft(parseIntSafe))) // Failure('Invalid number: x') . Signature . export declare const mapUnlessLeft: &lt;S extends MTypes.AnyReadonlyArray, B, C&gt;( f: (a: Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt;, i: number) =&gt; Result.Result&lt;B, C&gt; ) =&gt; (self: S) =&gt; Result.Result&lt;Array.ReadonlyArray.With&lt;S, B&gt;, C&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mapunlessleft", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mapunlessleft" },"11": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "mapUnlessNone", "content": "Maps every element of self with f, returning Option.some of the mapped array if every call succeeds, or Option.none as soon as one call returns Option.none. | Use when every element must be mappable for the operation to make sense. | Short-circuits on the first Option.none returned by f. | . Example (Map with possible failure) . import { Option, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const safeDiv = (x: number) =&gt; (x !== 0 ? Option.some(10 / x) : Option.none()) console.log(pipe([2, 5], MArray.mapUnlessNone(safeDiv))) // Some([5, 2]) console.log(pipe([2, 0, 5], MArray.mapUnlessNone(safeDiv))) // None . Signature . export declare const mapUnlessNone: &lt;S extends MTypes.AnyReadonlyArray, B&gt;( f: (a: Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt;, i: number) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;B&gt; ) =&gt; (self: S) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;Array.ReadonlyArray.With&lt;S, B&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mapunlessnone", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mapunlessnone" },"12": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "reduceUnlessLeft", "content": "Reduces self with f, returning Result.success of the final accumulator if every step succeeds, or the first failure encountered. | Use when reducing with a step that can produce a typed error. | Short-circuits on the first failure. | . Example (Reduce with error handling) . import { Result, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const safeSum = (acc: number, x: string) =&gt; { const n = parseInt(x) return Number.isNaN(n) ? Result.fail(`Invalid: ${x}`) : Result.succeed(acc + n) } console.log(pipe([\"1\", \"2\", \"3\"], MArray.reduceUnlessLeft(0, safeSum))) // Success(6) console.log(pipe([\"1\", \"x\", \"3\"], MArray.reduceUnlessLeft(0, safeSum))) // Failure('Invalid: x') . Signature . export declare const reduceUnlessLeft: &lt;B, A, C&gt;( b: B, f: (b: B, a: A, i: number) =&gt; Result.Result&lt;B, C&gt; ) =&gt; (self: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Result.Result&lt;B, C&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#reduceunlessleft", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#reduceunlessleft" },"13": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "reduceUnlessNone", "content": "Reduces self with f, returning Option.some of the final accumulator if every step succeeds, or Option.none as soon as one step returns Option.none. | Use when reducing with a step that may fail without context. | Short-circuits on the first Option.none. | . Example (Reduce with possible failure) . import { Option, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const safeAdd = (acc: number, x: number) =&gt; (x &gt;= 0 ? Option.some(acc + x) : Option.none()) console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.reduceUnlessNone(0, safeAdd))) // Some(6) console.log(pipe([1, -1, 3], MArray.reduceUnlessNone(0, safeAdd))) // None . Signature . export declare const reduceUnlessNone: &lt;B, A&gt;( b: B, f: (b: B, a: A, i: number) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;B&gt; ) =&gt; (self: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;B&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#reduceunlessnone", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#reduceunlessnone" },"14": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "unsafeGetter", "content": "Returns a function that retrieves the element of self at a given index without bounds checking. | Use to precompute an unchecked getter when the same array will be queried many times under a bounds invariant. | May return undefined (typed as A) for out-of-bounds indexes. | . Example (Reusable unsafe getter) . import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const get = MArray.unsafeGetter([1, 2, 3]) console.log(get(1)) // 2 . Signature . export declare const unsafeGetter: &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;number, A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unsafegetter", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unsafegetter" },"15": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#models" },"16": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Type (interface)", "content": "Type on which this module’s functions operate. Signature . export interface Type&lt;out A&gt; extends ReadonlyArray&lt;A&gt; {} . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#type-interface", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#type-interface" },"17": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Predicates", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#predicates", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#predicates" },"18": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "hasDuplicates", "content": "Returns true if self contains at least one duplicate, comparing elements with Equal.equals. | Use to validate uniqueness with default equality. | Comparison uses Effect’s Equal.equals (structural equality for Equal-aware types, otherwise ===). | . Example (Detecting duplicates) . import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(MArray.hasDuplicates([1, 2, 2, 3])) // true console.log(MArray.hasDuplicates([1, 2, 3])) // false . Signature . export declare const hasDuplicates: (self: Type&lt;unknown&gt;) =&gt; boolean . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#hasduplicates", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#hasduplicates" },"19": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "hasDuplicatesWith", "content": "Returns true if self contains at least one duplicate, comparing elements with the supplied Equivalence. | Use when default equality is not adequate (e.g. comparing objects by a single field). | Returns false for arrays with all-distinct elements. | . Example (Detecting duplicates with a custom equivalence) . import { Equivalence, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const byId = Equivalence.mapInput(Equivalence.number, (o: { readonly id: number }) =&gt; o.id) console.log(pipe([{ id: 1 }, { id: 1 }], MArray.hasDuplicatesWith(byId))) // true console.log(pipe([{ id: 1 }, { id: 2 }], MArray.hasDuplicatesWith(byId))) // false . Signature . export declare const hasDuplicatesWith: &lt;A&gt;( isEquivalent: Equivalence.Equivalence&lt;NoInfer&lt;A&gt;&gt; ) =&gt; (self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; boolean . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#hasduplicateswith", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#hasduplicateswith" },"20": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "hasLength", "content": "Returns true if the length of self is exactly l. | Use to assert that an array has a specific number of elements. | Length comparison is ===. | . Example (Length check) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.hasLength(3))) // true console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.hasLength(2))) // false . Signature . export declare const hasLength: (l: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; boolean . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#haslength", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#haslength" },"21": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Utility types", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#utility-types", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#utility-types" },"22": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "With (type alias)", "content": "Utility type that replaces the type of every element of an array or tuple with A. Signature . export type With&lt;S extends MTypes.AnyReadonlyArray, A&gt; = { [k in keyof S]: A } . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#with-type-alias", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#with-type-alias" },"23": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Utils", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#utils", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#utils" },"24": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "differenceSorted", "content": "Returns the elements of self not present in that. Both iterables must already be sorted according to o. Element equality is Equal.equals. | Use to compute a sorted set difference in a single linear pass. | Both inputs must be sorted; otherwise the result is undefined. | . Example (Sorted difference) . import { Order, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], MArray.differenceSorted(Order.number)([2, 4]))) // [1, 3, 5] . Signature . export declare const differenceSorted: &lt;A&gt;(o: Order.Order&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; (that: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; (self: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#differencesorted", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#differencesorted" },"25": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "extractFirst", "content": "Extracts the first element of self matching predicate (or refinement) and returns a pair of the extracted element (as an Option) and the remaining elements in their original order. | Use to find and remove the first matching element in a single pass. | When no element matches, returns [Option.none(), self]. | Acts as a refinement-aware destructor: the extracted element is narrowed when a refinement is supplied. | . Example (Extract first matching element) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const [match, rest] = pipe( [1, 3, 2, 4], MArray.extractFirst((n) =&gt; n &gt; 2) ) console.log(match) // Some(3) console.log(rest) // [1, 2, 4] . Signature . export declare const extractFirst: { &lt;A, B extends A&gt;( refinement: (a: NoInfer&lt;A&gt;, i: number) =&gt; a is B ): (self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; MTypes.Pair&lt;Option.Option&lt;B&gt;, Array&lt;A&gt;&gt; &lt;A&gt;(predicate: (a: NoInfer&lt;A&gt;, i: number) =&gt; boolean): (self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; MTypes.Pair&lt;Option.Option&lt;A&gt;, Array&lt;A&gt;&gt; } . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#extractfirst", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#extractfirst" },"26": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "findAll", "content": "Returns the indexes of all elements of self satisfying predicate, in ascending order. | Use to locate every position matching a condition. | Returns an empty array when no element matches. | . Example (Indexes of matching elements) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" import * as MPredicate from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MPredicate\" console.log(pipe([1, 3, 2, 4], MArray.findAll(MPredicate.strictEquals(3)))) // [1] console.log(pipe([1, 3, 2, 4, 3], MArray.findAll(MPredicate.strictEquals(3)))) // [1, 4] . Signature . export declare const findAll: &lt;A&gt;(predicate: Predicate.Predicate&lt;NoInfer&lt;A&gt;&gt;) =&gt; (self: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#findall", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#findall" },"27": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "getFromEnd", "content": "Returns the element at position index counted from the end of self as an Option. | Use to access from the tail of an array. | index is zero-based: 0 is the last element. | Returns Option.none when index is out of bounds. | . Example (Indexed access from the end) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.getFromEnd(0))) // Some(3) console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.getFromEnd(1))) // Some(2) console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.getFromEnd(3))) // None . Signature . export declare const getFromEnd: (index: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#getfromend", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#getfromend" },"28": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "groupBy", "content": "Like Array.groupBy but applies fValue to each element before collecting it into its bucket. | Use to group and project in a single pass. | Each bucket is guaranteed non-empty (typed MTypes.OverOne&lt;B&gt;). | . Example (Group with projection) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const data = [ { type: \"a\", value: 1 }, { type: \"a\", value: 2 }, { type: \"b\", value: 3 } ] as const console.log(pipe(data, MArray.groupBy({ fKey: (item) =&gt; item.type, fValue: (item) =&gt; item.value }))) // { a: [1, 2], b: [3] } . Signature . export declare const groupBy: &lt;A, B&gt;({ fKey, fValue }: { readonly fKey: (a: NoInfer&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; string readonly fValue: (a: NoInfer&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; B }) =&gt; (self: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Record&lt;string, MTypes.OverOne&lt;B&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#groupby", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#groupby" },"29": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "groupByNum", "content": "Maps the elements of self with fValue and groups the results by the numeric index returned by fKey. The output is an array of length size. Elements whose key is negative or &gt;= size are dropped; rows for which no element maps are left as empty arrays. | Use to bucket elements into a fixed number of slots. | Together with {@link ungroup} provides a round-trip: groupByNum reverses ungroup. | . Example (Bucketing by row index) . import { Tuple, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const input = [ [0, \"a\"], [0, \"b\"], [1, \"c\"], [1, \"d\"] ] as ReadonlyArray&lt;[number, string]&gt; console.log(pipe(input, MArray.groupByNum({ size: 2, fKey: Tuple.get(0), fValue: Tuple.get(1) }))) // [['a', 'b'], ['c', 'd']] . Signature . export declare const groupByNum: &lt;A, B&gt;({ size, fKey, fValue }: { readonly size: number readonly fKey: (a: NoInfer&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; number readonly fValue: (a: NoInfer&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; B }) =&gt; (self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; ReadonlyArray&lt;ReadonlyArray&lt;B&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#groupbynum", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#groupbynum" },"30": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "longestCommonSubArray", "content": "Returns the longest common prefix of self and that, comparing elements with Equal.equals. | Use to find the leading elements two arrays agree on. | Returns an empty array when the first elements already differ. | . Example (Longest common prefix) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 4], MArray.longestCommonSubArray([1, 2, 3]))) // [1, 2] console.log(pipe([0, 1], MArray.longestCommonSubArray([1, 2]))) // [] . Signature . export declare const longestCommonSubArray: &lt;A&gt;(that: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; (self: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#longestcommonsubarray", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#longestcommonsubarray" },"31": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "match012", "content": "Pattern-matches self by cardinality: empty, singleton, or two-or-more. | Use to branch type-safely on array size. | onSingleton receives the single element directly. | onOverTwo receives self typed as MTypes.ReadonlyOverTwo&lt;A&gt; (two-or-more). | . Example (Cardinality match) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" const describe = MArray.match012({ onEmpty: () =&gt; \"empty\", onSingleton: (x: number) =&gt; `one: ${x}`, onOverTwo: (xs) =&gt; `many: ${xs.length}` }) console.log(pipe([], describe)) // 'empty' console.log(pipe([1], describe)) // 'one: 1' console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], describe)) // 'many: 3' . Signature . export declare const match012: &lt;A, B, C = B, D = B&gt;(options: { readonly onEmpty: Function.LazyArg&lt;B&gt; readonly onSingleton: (self: NoInfer&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; C readonly onOverTwo: (self: MTypes.ReadonlyOverTwo&lt;NoInfer&lt;A&gt;&gt;) =&gt; D }) =&gt; (self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; B | C | D . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#match012", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#match012" },"32": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "mergeSorted", "content": "Stably merges two iterables already sorted according to o. | Both inputs must already be sorted by o. | The merge is stable: equal elements from self precede equal elements from that. | . Example (Merge sorted iterables) . import { Order, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 3, 5], MArray.mergeSorted(Order.number)([2, 4, 6]))) // [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6] . Signature . export declare const mergeSorted: &lt;A&gt;(o: Order.Order&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; (that: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; (self: Iterable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mergesorted", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#mergesorted" },"33": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "modifyHead", "content": "Returns a copy of self with the first element transformed by f. | Use to update only the leading element. | Returns an empty copy when self is empty. | . Example (Modify first element) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log( pipe( [1, 2, 3], MArray.modifyHead((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [2, 2, 3] console.log( pipe( [], MArray.modifyHead((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [] . Signature . export declare const modifyHead: &lt;S extends MTypes.AnyReadonlyArray, B&gt;( f: (a: Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt;) =&gt; B ) =&gt; (self: S) =&gt; With&lt;S, Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt; | B&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifyhead", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifyhead" },"34": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "modifyInit", "content": "Returns a copy of self with every element except the last transformed by f. | Use to apply a transformation to all elements but the trailing one. | Returns self unchanged when it has zero or one elements. | . Example (Modify all but the last) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log( pipe( [1, 2, 3, 4], MArray.modifyInit((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [2, 4, 6, 4] console.log( pipe( [5], MArray.modifyInit((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [5] . Signature . export declare const modifyInit: &lt;S extends MTypes.AnyReadonlyArray, B&gt;( f: (a: Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt;, i: number) =&gt; B ) =&gt; (self: S) =&gt; With&lt;S, Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt; | B&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifyinit", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifyinit" },"35": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "modifyLast", "content": "Returns a copy of self with the last element transformed by f. | Use to update only the trailing element. | Returns an empty copy when self is empty. | . Example (Modify last element) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log( pipe( [1, 2, 3], MArray.modifyLast((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [1, 2, 6] console.log( pipe( [], MArray.modifyLast((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [] . Signature . export declare const modifyLast: &lt;S extends MTypes.AnyReadonlyArray, B&gt;( f: (a: Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt;) =&gt; B ) =&gt; (self: S) =&gt; With&lt;S, Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt; | B&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifylast", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifylast" },"36": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "modifyTail", "content": "Returns a copy of self with every element except the first transformed by f. | Use to apply a transformation to all elements but the leading one. | Returns self unchanged when it has zero or one elements. | . Example (Modify all but the first) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log( pipe( [1, 2, 3, 4], MArray.modifyTail((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [1, 4, 6, 8] console.log( pipe( [5], MArray.modifyTail((x) =&gt; x * 2) ) ) // [5] . Signature . export declare const modifyTail: &lt;S extends MTypes.AnyReadonlyArray, B&gt;( f: (a: Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt;, i: number) =&gt; B ) =&gt; (self: S) =&gt; With&lt;S, Array.ReadonlyArray.Infer&lt;S&gt; | B&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifytail", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#modifytail" },"37": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "pad", "content": "Same as Array.pad but the result is typed as a fixed-size Tuple of length N instead of a plain array. | Use when the resulting length is part of the type and downstream code relies on it. | Pads with fill when shorter than n; truncates when longer. | . Example (Padding to a fixed length) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.pad(5, 0))) // [1, 2, 3, 0, 0] . Signature . export declare const pad: &lt;A, T, N extends number&gt;( n: N, fill: T ) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type&lt;A&gt;, MTypes.Tuple&lt;A | T, N&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#pad", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#pad" },"38": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "removeEmptyAndJoin", "content": "Joins the strings of self with sep, ignoring empty strings so they do not introduce extra separators. | Use when assembling fragments coming from heterogeneous sources where some may be empty. | The output never contains two consecutive sep’s nor a leading/trailing sep. | . Example (Joining without empty fragments) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([\"a\", \"\", \"b\", \"\", \"c\"], MArray.removeEmptyAndJoin(\", \"))) // 'a, b, c' . Signature . export declare const removeEmptyAndJoin: (sep: string) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Iterable&lt;string&gt;, string&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#removeemptyandjoin", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#removeemptyandjoin" },"39": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "splitAtFromRight", "content": "Splits self into two segments, the second containing at most the last n elements. | Use to take a fixed-size suffix while keeping the rest. | When n &gt;= self.length, the first segment is empty. | n must be a non-negative integer; 0 puts everything in the first segment. | . Example (Split from the right) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], MArray.splitAtFromRight(2))) // [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5]] console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.splitAtFromRight(0))) // [[1, 2, 3], []] . Signature . export declare const splitAtFromRight: (n: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; [beforeIndex: Array&lt;A&gt;, fromIndex: Array&lt;A&gt;] . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#splitatfromright", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#splitatfromright" },"40": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "splitNonEmptyAtFromRight", "content": "Variant of {@link splitAtFromRight} for non-empty arrays where the second segment is guaranteed non-empty. | n must be &gt;= 1. | Returns the second segment typed as MTypes.OverOne&lt;A&gt;. | . Example (Non-empty split from the right) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3, 4] as const, MArray.splitNonEmptyAtFromRight(2))) // [[1, 2], [3, 4]] . Signature . export declare const splitNonEmptyAtFromRight: ( n: number ) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: MTypes.ReadonlyOverOne&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; [beforeIndex: Array&lt;A&gt;, fromIndex: MTypes.OverOne&lt;A&gt;] . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#splitnonemptyatfromright", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#splitnonemptyatfromright" },"41": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "takeBut", "content": "Returns all elements of self except the last n. | Use to drop a suffix of fixed size. | When n &gt;= self.length, returns an empty array. | n should be a non-negative integer. | . Example (Drop trailing elements) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3, 4], MArray.takeBut(2))) // [1, 2] console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.takeBut(5))) // [] . Signature . export declare const takeBut: (n: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#takebut", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#takebut" },"42": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "takeRightBut", "content": "Returns all elements of self except the first n. | Use to drop a prefix of fixed size. | When n &gt;= self.length, returns an empty array. | n should be a non-negative integer. | . Example (Drop leading elements) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3, 4], MArray.takeRightBut(2))) // [3, 4] console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.takeRightBut(5))) // [] . Signature . export declare const takeRightBut: (n: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#takerightbut", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#takerightbut" },"43": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "ungroup", "content": "Flattens a two-dimensional array, tagging each element with the index of its source row. | Use as the inverse companion to {@link groupByNum}: groupByNum undoes ungroup when fKey/fValue extract the row index and the original element respectively. | Order is preserved: rows are visited in order, and each row is flattened left to right. | . Example (Tagged flatten) . import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log( MArray.ungroup([ [1, 2, 3], [4, 5] ]) ) // [[0, 1], [0, 2], [0, 3], [1, 4], [1, 5]] . Signature . export declare const ungroup: &lt;A&gt;(as: Type&lt;Type&lt;A&gt;&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;[number, A]&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#ungroup", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#ungroup" },"44": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "unsafeGet", "content": "Returns the element of self at index without bounds checking. | Use only when bounds are guaranteed by construction; otherwise prefer Array.get. | Returns undefined (typed as A) for out-of-bounds indexes. | . Example (Unchecked access) . import { pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MArray from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MArray\" console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.unsafeGet(0))) // 1 console.log(pipe([1, 2, 3], MArray.unsafeGet(10))) // undefined . Signature . export declare const unsafeGet: (index: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; A . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unsafeget", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html#unsafeget" },"45": { "doc": "Array.ts", "title": "Array.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Array.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Array.ts.html" },"46": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "BigDecimal overview", "content": "Extension to the Effect BigDecimal module providing safe constructors from primitives and truncation utilities. ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#bigdecimal-overview", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#bigdecimal-overview" },"47": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Mental model", "content": ". | BigDecimal is an arbitrary-precision decimal: a bigint value paired with a scale (the number of decimal digits). | This module focuses on safely building BigDecimal’s from JavaScript primitives and on truncating their fractional part. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#mental-model", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#mental-model" },"48": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Common tasks", "content": ". | Construct: {@link fromPrimitiveOption} | Instances: {@link zero} | Truncate: {@link trunc}, {@link truncatedAndFollowingParts} | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#common-tasks", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#common-tasks" },"49": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Quickstart", "content": "Example (Construction and truncation) . import { Option, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MBigDecimal from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigDecimal\" const bd = pipe(\"3.14\", MBigDecimal.fromPrimitiveOption(2), Option.getOrThrow) console.log(pipe(bd, MBigDecimal.trunc(1))) // BigDecimal(31, 1) i.e. 3.1 . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#quickstart", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#quickstart" },"50": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constructors . | fromPrimitiveOption | . | Destructors . | truncatedAndFollowingParts | . | Instances . | zero | . | Models . | Type (type alias) | . | Utils . | trunc | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html" },"51": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#constructors" },"52": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "fromPrimitiveOption", "content": "Builds a BigDecimal from a string, number or boolean paired with scale. Returns Option.none when the primitive cannot be converted to a bigint. | Use to build a BigDecimal from untrusted input without risking an exception. | scale is the number of decimal digits attached to the resulting value. | . Example (Safe construction) . import * as MBigDecimal from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigDecimal\" console.log(MBigDecimal.fromPrimitiveOption(2)(\"3.14\")) // Some(BigDecimal(314, 2)) console.log(MBigDecimal.fromPrimitiveOption(2)(\"abc\")) // None . Signature . export declare const fromPrimitiveOption: ( scale: number ) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;string | number | boolean, Option.Option&lt;BigDecimal.BigDecimal&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#fromprimitiveoption", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#fromprimitiveoption" },"53": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Destructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#destructors", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#destructors" },"54": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "truncatedAndFollowingParts", "content": "Splits self into [truncatedPart, followingPart] where truncatedPart is self truncated after precision decimal digits and followingPart is self - truncatedPart. | Use when both the truncated value and its remainder are needed (e.g. when building digit-by-digit formatters). | precision must be a non-negative finite integer; defaults to 0. | . Example (Separating truncated and remainder parts) . import { Option, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MBigDecimal from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigDecimal\" const bd = pipe(\"3.14159\", MBigDecimal.fromPrimitiveOption(5), Option.getOrThrow) const [truncated, following] = pipe(bd, MBigDecimal.truncatedAndFollowingParts(2)) // truncated ≡ 3.14, following ≡ 0.00159 . Signature . export declare const truncatedAndFollowingParts: ( precision?: number ) =&gt; (self: Type) =&gt; [truncatedPart: BigDecimal.BigDecimal, followingPart: BigDecimal.BigDecimal] . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#truncatedandfollowingparts", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#truncatedandfollowingparts" },"55": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Instances", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#instances", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#instances" },"56": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "zero", "content": "BigDecimal instance representing 0. Signature . export declare const zero: BigDecimal.BigDecimal . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#zero", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#zero" },"57": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#models" },"58": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Type (type alias)", "content": "Type on which this module’s functions operate. Signature . export type Type = BigDecimal.BigDecimal . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#type-type-alias", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#type-type-alias" },"59": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "Utils", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#utils", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#utils" },"60": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "trunc", "content": "Truncates a BigDecimal after precision decimal digits. | Use to drop fractional digits beyond a given precision. | Rounds towards zero. | precision must be a non-negative finite integer; defaults to 0. | . Example (Truncate to a given precision) . import { Option, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MBigDecimal from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigDecimal\" const bd = pipe(\"3.14159\", MBigDecimal.fromPrimitiveOption(5), Option.getOrThrow) console.log(pipe(bd, MBigDecimal.trunc(2))) // BigDecimal(314, 2) i.e. 3.14 . Signature . export declare const trunc: (precision?: number) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#trunc", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html#trunc" },"61": { "doc": "BigDecimal.ts", "title": "BigDecimal.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigDecimal.ts.html" },"62": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "BigInt overview", "content": "Extension to the Effect BigInt module providing safe constructors from primitives, parity predicates, and a base-10 logarithm. ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#bigint-overview", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#bigint-overview" },"63": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Mental model", "content": ". | bigint is JavaScript’s built-in arbitrary-precision integer. | This module focuses on safe construction (fromPrimitive*), parity predicates, and a linear-time base-10 logarithm computed from the decimal representation. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#mental-model", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#mental-model" },"64": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Common tasks", "content": ". | Construct: {@link fromPrimitiveOrThrow}, {@link fromPrimitiveOption} | Predicates: {@link isEven}, {@link isOdd} | Destructors: {@link log10}, {@link unsafeLog10} | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#common-tasks", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#common-tasks" },"65": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Quickstart", "content": "Example (Safe construction and parity) . import * as MBigInt from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigInt\" console.log(MBigInt.fromPrimitiveOption(\"123\")) // Some(123n) console.log(MBigInt.fromPrimitiveOption(\"abc\")) // None console.log(MBigInt.isEven(4n)) // true console.log(MBigInt.log10(100n)) // Some(2) . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#quickstart", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#quickstart" },"66": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constructors . | fromPrimitiveOption | fromPrimitiveOrThrow | . | Destructors . | log10 | unsafeLog10 | . | Models . | Type (type alias) | . | Predicates . | isEven | isOdd | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html" },"67": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#constructors" },"68": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "fromPrimitiveOption", "content": "Same as {@link fromPrimitiveOrThrow} but returns Option.none instead of throwing on invalid input. | Use to build a bigint from untrusted input. | . Example (Safe construction) . import * as MBigInt from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigInt\" console.log(MBigInt.fromPrimitiveOption(\"123\")) // Some(123n) console.log(MBigInt.fromPrimitiveOption(\"abc\")) // None . Signature . export declare const fromPrimitiveOption: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;string | number | boolean, Option.Option&lt;bigint&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#fromprimitiveoption", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#fromprimitiveoption" },"69": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "fromPrimitiveOrThrow", "content": "Builds a bigint from a string, number, or boolean. Throws when the input cannot be converted (e.g. NaN, non-integer numbers, malformed strings). | Use when an exception on invalid input is acceptable (e.g. trusted constants). | For untrusted input, prefer {@link fromPrimitiveOption}. | . Example (Throwing constructor) . import * as MBigInt from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigInt\" console.log(MBigInt.fromPrimitiveOrThrow(\"123\")) // 123n console.log(MBigInt.fromPrimitiveOrThrow(true)) // 1n . Signature . export declare const fromPrimitiveOrThrow: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;string | number | boolean, bigint&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#fromprimitiveorthrow", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#fromprimitiveorthrow" },"70": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Destructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#destructors", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#destructors" },"71": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "log10", "content": "Safe variant of {@link unsafeLog10}: returns Option.some(floor(log10(self))) for strictly positive self, otherwise Option.none. | Returns Option.none for 0n and for strictly negative values. | . Example (Safe base-10 logarithm) . import * as MBigInt from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigInt\" console.log(MBigInt.log10(100n)) // Some(2) console.log(MBigInt.log10(0n)) // None console.log(MBigInt.log10(-5n)) // None . Signature . export declare const log10: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;bigint, Option.Option&lt;number&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#log10", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#log10" },"72": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "unsafeLog10", "content": "Returns floor(log10(self)) (i.e. one less than the number of decimal digits) without input validation. | Use when self is statically known to be strictly positive. | Computed from the length of the decimal representation of self. | For non-positive input the result is meaningless: unsafeLog10(0n) returns 0, and for negative values the leading '-' sign is counted as a digit. | . Example (Unchecked base-10 logarithm) . import * as MBigInt from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigInt\" console.log(MBigInt.unsafeLog10(100n)) // 2 console.log(MBigInt.unsafeLog10(10n)) // 1 . Signature . export declare const unsafeLog10: (self: Type) =&gt; number . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#unsafelog10", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#unsafelog10" },"73": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#models" },"74": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Type (type alias)", "content": "Type on which this module’s functions operate. Signature . export type Type = bigint . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#type-type-alias", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#type-type-alias" },"75": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "Predicates", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#predicates", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#predicates" },"76": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "isEven", "content": "Returns true when self is even. Example (Even check) . import * as MBigInt from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigInt\" console.log(MBigInt.isEven(4n)) // true console.log(MBigInt.isEven(5n)) // false . Signature . export declare const isEven: Predicate.Predicate&lt;bigint&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#iseven", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#iseven" },"77": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "isOdd", "content": "Returns true when self is odd. Example (Odd check) . import * as MBigInt from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MBigInt\" console.log(MBigInt.isOdd(5n)) // true console.log(MBigInt.isOdd(4n)) // false . Signature . export declare const isOdd: Predicate.Predicate&lt;bigint&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#isodd", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html#isodd" },"78": { "doc": "BigInt.ts", "title": "BigInt.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/BigInt.ts.html" },"79": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "ByPasser overview", "content": "This module implements a type that can optionally short-circuit the normal stringification pipeline for a given non-primitive value. When a PPByPasser decides to handle a value it returns a some of the resulting string, bypassing the usual property-extraction and formatting steps. When it does not apply, it returns a none and the normal pipeline takes over. A typical use case is printing a Date as a human-readable string rather than as an object with all its internal properties. Use the make function to define custom instances if the pre-built ones do not suit your needs. ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#bypasser-overview", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#bypasser-overview" },"80": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constructors . | make | merge | . | Equivalences . | equivalence | . | Getters . | action | id | . | Instances . | allWithName | dateAndRegExp | empty | toStringable | . | Models . | Type (class) . | [MData.idSymbol] (method) | [Hash.symbol] (method) | [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.isEquivalentToSymbol] (method) | [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.hasSameTypeMarkerAsSymbol] (method) | id (property) | action (property) | . | . | Module markers . | moduleTag | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html" },"81": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#constructors" },"82": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "make", "content": "Constructor of a PPByPasser . Signature . export declare const make: (params: MTypes.Data&lt;Type&gt;) =&gt; Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#make", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#make" },"83": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "merge", "content": "Creates a new PPByPasser by composing several existing PPByPasser’s. The resulting PPByPasser returns the some of the first PPByPasser in byPassers that returns a some for the given value. Returns none if no PPByPasser matches. Signature . export declare const merge: ({ id, byPassers }: { readonly id: string readonly byPassers: ReadonlyArray&lt;Type&gt; }) =&gt; Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#merge", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#merge" },"84": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Equivalences", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#equivalences", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#equivalences" },"85": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "equivalence", "content": "Equivalence . Signature . export declare const equivalence: Equivalence.Equivalence&lt;Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#equivalence", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#equivalence" },"86": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Getters", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#getters", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#getters" },"87": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "action", "content": "Returns the action property of self . Signature . export declare const action: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt; Type, MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt; { readonly nonPrimitive: PPValue.ReadonlyNonPrimitive readonly parameters: PPParameters.Type readonly applicableNonPrimitiveParameters: PPResolvedNonPrimitiveParameters.Type }, Option.Option&lt;string&gt; &gt; &gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#action", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#action" },"88": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "id", "content": "Returns the id property of self . Signature . export declare const id: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, string&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#id", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#id" },"89": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Instances", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#instances", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#instances" },"90": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "allWithName", "content": "PPByPasser instance that displays the non-primitive value as its name surrounded by the openingTagMark and closingTagMark (e.g. [Function: foo]). Always returns a some. Can be used to display functions. Signature . export declare const allWithName: Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#allwithname", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#allwithname" },"91": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "dateAndRegExp", "content": "PPByPasser instance that: . | Returns a some of the result of calling .toISOString() on a Date non-primitive value | Returns a some of the result of calling .toString() on a RegExp non-primitive value | Returns a none for all other non-primitive values | . This is the default byPasser baked into the merge defaults, so dates and regular expressions are pretty-printed as 2026-04-29T00:00:00.000Z and /foo/g even when no PPNonPrimitiveParameters explicitly sets a byPasser. Signature . export declare const dateAndRegExp: Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#dateandregexp", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#dateandregexp" },"92": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "empty", "content": "PPByPasser instance that never bypasses any value (always returns none) . Signature . export declare const empty: Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#empty", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#empty" },"93": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "toStringable", "content": "PPByPasser instance that calls the .toString() method of the non-primitive value, but only when that method is not Object.prototype.toString (i.e. the value has a custom or overridden implementation). Returns a some of the result on success, none otherwise. Practical examples where this returns a some: Date, any class that overrides toString. Note that calling .toString() on a function will return its source code, which is usually not the desired output. Signature . export declare const toStringable: Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#tostringable", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#tostringable" },"94": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#models" },"95": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Type (class)", "content": "Type that represents a PPByPasser . Signature . export declare class Type { constructor({ id, action }: MTypes.Data&lt;Type&gt;) } . [MData.idSymbol] (method) . Returns the id of this . Signature . [MData.idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string) . [Hash.symbol] (method) . Calculates the hash value of this . Signature . [Hash.symbol](): number . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.isEquivalentToSymbol] (method) . Function that implements the equivalence of this and that . Signature . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.isEquivalentToSymbol](this: this, that: this): boolean . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.hasSameTypeMarkerAsSymbol] (method) . Predicate that returns true if that has the same type marker as this . Signature . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.hasSameTypeMarkerAsSymbol](that: unknown): boolean . id (property) . Id of this PPByPasser instance. Useful for equality and debugging . Signature . readonly id: string . action (property) . Action of this PPByPasser. Takes as input: . | nonPrimitive: the non-primitive value being stringified (used as context for styling), | parameters: the PPParameters instance passed to the PPStringifier, | applicableNonPrimitiveParameters: the merged, fully-resolved PPNonPrimitiveParameters fields applicable to nonPrimitive (see PPResolvedNonPrimitiveParameters.fromApplicableNonPrimitiveParameters). | . Returns Option.some(s) where s is the bypass string when this bypasser handles the value. Signature . readonly action: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;{ readonly nonPrimitive: PPValue.ReadonlyNonPrimitive; readonly parameters: PPParameters.Type; readonly applicableNonPrimitiveParameters: PPResolvedNonPrimitiveParameters.Type; }, Option.Option&lt;string&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#type-class", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#type-class" },"96": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Module markers", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#module-markers", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#module-markers" },"97": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "moduleTag", "content": "Module tag . Signature . export declare const moduleTag: \"@parischap/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser/\" . ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#moduletag", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html#moduletag" },"98": { "doc": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "title": "Parameters/ByPasser.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html", "relUrl": "/pretty-print/Parameters/ByPasser.ts.html" },"99": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Cache overview", "content": "Mutable cache with optional bounded capacity and optional time-to-live built around a user-supplied lookup function. The lookup function may be recursive, in which case the cache is also used to detect circularity. ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#cache-overview", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#cache-overview" },"100": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Mental model", "content": ". | Type&lt;A, B&gt; is a mutable store mapping keys of type A to values of type B, populated on demand by lookUp. | Keys are compared with Equal.equals (the underlying store is a MutableHashMap). | Eviction is FIFO: when capacity is exceeded the oldest insertion is evicted first. | When lifeSpan elapses for an entry, the next read triggers a fresh lookup; entries inserted before the expired one are also evicted in the process to keep insertion order consistent with age. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#mental-model", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#mental-model" },"101": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Common tasks", "content": ". | Construct: {@link make} | Read: {@link get}, {@link toGetter} | Inspect: {@link toKeys} | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#common-tasks", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#common-tasks" },"102": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Gotchas", "content": ". | The cache is mutable — get mutates the underlying store. Sharing a cache across fibers without external coordination is unsafe. | When the lookup function is recursive, capacity may be temporarily exceeded: every key in the recursion chain is reserved (with an empty entry) before a result is produced, so a chain of n recursive calls reserves n entries even past capacity. Excess entries are reclaimed once the recursion unwinds. | When isCircular is true, the value returned by lookUp is never stored, regardless of the second tuple element. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#gotchas", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#gotchas" },"103": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Quickstart", "content": "Example (Basic cache usage) . import { Tuple, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MCache from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MCache\" const cache = MCache.make({ lookUp: ({ key }: { readonly key: number }) =&gt; Tuple.make(key * 2, true) }) console.log(pipe(cache, MCache.get(5))) // 10 . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#quickstart", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#quickstart" },"104": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constructors . | make | . | Models . | LookUp (interface) | Type (class) . | make (static method) | [MData.idSymbol] (method) | store (property) | keyListInOrder (property) | lookUp (property) | capacity (property) | lifeSpan (property) | . | . | Module markers . | moduleTag | . | Utils . | get | toGetter | toKeys | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html" },"105": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#constructors" },"106": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "make", "content": "Builds a new cache backed by lookUp. | Use to wrap an expensive function in a cache. Keys are compared with Equal.equals. | capacity defaults to Infinity (unbounded). | lifeSpan defaults to Infinity (entries never expire). | . Example (Bounded cache with TTL) . import { Tuple } from \"effect\" import * as MCache from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MCache\" const cache = MCache.make({ lookUp: ({ key }: { readonly key: number }) =&gt; Tuple.make(key * 2, true), capacity: 100, lifeSpan: 60_000 // 1 minute }) . Signature . export declare const make: &lt;A, B&gt;({ lookUp, capacity, lifeSpan }: { readonly lookUp: LookUp&lt;A, B&gt; readonly capacity?: number readonly lifeSpan?: number }) =&gt; Type&lt;A, B&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#make", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#make" },"107": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#models" },"108": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "LookUp (interface)", "content": "Type of the lookup function passed to {@link make}. The lookup receives a record carrying the key to look up, an isCircular flag, and a memoized callback that re-enters the cache recursively when isCircular is false. | The function returns a [result, storeInCache] tuple. storeInCache only acts as a hint: when isCircular is true, the value is never stored regardless of storeInCache. | Use the memoized parameter inside the lookup body to recurse through the cache instead of calling the lookup directly; this enables circularity detection. | . Signature . export interface LookUp&lt;A, B&gt; extends MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt; | { readonly key: A; readonly memoized: undefined; readonly isCircular: true } | { readonly key: A; readonly memoized: (a: A) =&gt; B; readonly isCircular: false }, MTypes.Pair&lt;B, boolean&gt; &gt; {} . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#lookup-interface", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#lookup-interface" },"109": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Type (class)", "content": "Type of a cache. Signature . export declare class Type&lt;A, B&gt; { private constructor(params: MTypes.Data&lt;Type&lt;A, B&gt;&gt;) } . make (static method) . Static constructor. Signature . static make&lt;A, B&gt;(params: MTypes.Data&lt;Type&lt;A, B&gt;&gt;): Type&lt;A, B&gt; . [MData.idSymbol] (method) . Returns the id of this. Signature . [MData.idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string) . store (property) . The underlying store. A key mapped to Option.none means a lookup is currently in progress (used to detect circular recursion). Signature . readonly store: MutableHashMap.MutableHashMap&lt;A, Option.Option&lt;MCacheValueContainer.Type&lt;B&gt;&gt;&gt; . keyListInOrder (property) . The order in which keys were inserted, used to evict the oldest first when the cache reaches its capacity. Signature . readonly keyListInOrder: MutableList.MutableList&lt;A&gt; . lookUp (property) . The lookup function used to populate the cache. Signature . readonly lookUp: LookUp&lt;A, B&gt; . capacity (property) . The capacity of the cache. Infinity means unbounded; NaN or a negative value is normalized to 0. Signature . readonly capacity: number . lifeSpan (property) . The lifespan of cached values, in milliseconds. Infinity means values never expire; NaN or a negative value is normalized to 0. A 0 lifespan means every subsequent lookup considers the entry expired. Signature . readonly lifeSpan: number . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#type-class", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#type-class" },"110": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Module markers", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#module-markers", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#module-markers" },"111": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "moduleTag", "content": "Module tag. Signature . export declare const moduleTag: \"@parischap/effect-lib/Cache/\" . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#moduletag", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#moduletag" },"112": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Utils", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#utils", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#utils" },"113": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "get", "content": "Reads the value associated with a from self. Triggers a lookup when the key is missing or its entry has expired. | Keys are compared with Equal.equals. | When the lookup is already in progress for a (recursive call), lookUp is invoked with isCircular: true and the returned value is not stored. | On expiration of an entry, every entry inserted before it is evicted as well to keep the FIFO insertion order in sync with element age. | . Example (Reading from the cache) . import { Tuple, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MCache from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MCache\" const cache = MCache.make({ lookUp: ({ key }: { readonly key: number }) =&gt; Tuple.make(key * 2, true) }) console.log(pipe(cache, MCache.get(5))) // 10 . Signature . export declare const get: &lt;A&gt;(a: A) =&gt; &lt;B&gt;(self: Type&lt;A, B&gt;) =&gt; B . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#get", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#get" },"114": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "toGetter", "content": "Returns a getter bound to self, suitable for point-free lookups. | Use when the same cache will be queried by many call sites and you want to capture it once. | Equivalent to (a) =&gt; MCache.get(a)(self). | . Example (Reusable getter) . import { Tuple } from \"effect\" import * as MCache from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MCache\" const cache = MCache.make({ lookUp: ({ key }: { readonly key: number }) =&gt; Tuple.make(key * 2, true) }) const lookup = MCache.toGetter(cache) console.log(lookup(5)) // 10 . Signature . export declare const toGetter: &lt;A, B&gt;(self: Type&lt;A, B&gt;) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;A, B&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#togetter", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#togetter" },"115": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "toKeys", "content": "Returns the keys whose value is currently present in the cache. | Keys whose lookup is in progress (i.e. mapped to Option.none) are excluded. | The order of the returned array reflects the iteration order of the underlying MutableHashMap, which is implementation-defined. | . Example (Listing cached keys) . import { Tuple, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MCache from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MCache\" const cache = MCache.make({ lookUp: ({ key }: { readonly key: number }) =&gt; Tuple.make(key * 2, true) }) pipe(cache, MCache.get(1)) pipe(cache, MCache.get(2)) console.log(MCache.toKeys(cache)) // [1, 2] . Signature . export declare const toKeys: &lt;A, B&gt;(self: Type&lt;A, B&gt;) =&gt; Array&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#tokeys", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html#tokeys" },"116": { "doc": "Cache.ts", "title": "Cache.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Cache.ts.html" },"117": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Chunk overview", "content": "Extension to the Effect Chunk module providing length and duplicate predicates, indexed search, and slicing operations. ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#chunk-overview", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#chunk-overview" },"118": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Mental model", "content": ". | Chunk.Chunk&lt;A&gt; is an immutable, persistent sequence of elements of type A. | All functions return new chunks; chunks are never mutated. | Functions are curried, data-last — call as MChunk.fn(arg)(chunk) or pipe(chunk, MChunk.fn(arg)). They are not data-first/data-last dual. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#mental-model", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#mental-model" },"119": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Common tasks", "content": ". | Query: {@link hasLength}, {@link hasDuplicates} | Search: {@link findAll} | Slice: {@link takeBut}, {@link takeRightBut} | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#common-tasks", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#common-tasks" },"120": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Quickstart", "content": "Example (Indexed search and duplicate check) . import { Chunk, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MChunk from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MChunk\" import * as MPredicate from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MPredicate\" const chunk = Chunk.make(1, 2, 3, 2, 4) console.log(MChunk.hasDuplicates(chunk)) // true console.log(pipe(chunk, MChunk.findAll(MPredicate.strictEquals(2)))) // Chunk(1, 3) . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#quickstart", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#quickstart" },"121": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Models . | Type (interface) | . | Predicates . | hasDuplicates | hasLength | . | Utils . | findAll | takeBut | takeRightBut | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html" },"122": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#models" },"123": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Type (interface)", "content": "Type on which this module’s functions operate. Signature . export interface Type&lt;out A&gt; extends Chunk.Chunk&lt;A&gt; {} . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#type-interface", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#type-interface" },"124": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Predicates", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#predicates", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#predicates" },"125": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "hasDuplicates", "content": "Returns true if self contains at least one duplicate, using Equal.equals for comparison. | Use to validate uniqueness constraints. | Comparison uses Effect’s Equal.equals (structural equality for Equal-aware types, otherwise ===). | Returns false for empty chunks. | . Example (Detecting duplicates) . import { Chunk } from \"effect\" import * as MChunk from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MChunk\" console.log(MChunk.hasDuplicates(Chunk.make(1, 2, 3))) // false console.log(MChunk.hasDuplicates(Chunk.make(1, 2, 2, 3))) // true . Signature . export declare const hasDuplicates: &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; boolean . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#hasduplicates", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#hasduplicates" },"126": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "hasLength", "content": "Returns true if the length of self is exactly l. | Use to assert that a chunk has a specific number of elements. | Length comparison is ===. | . Example (Length check) . import { Chunk, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MChunk from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MChunk\" const chunk = Chunk.make(1, 2, 3) console.log(pipe(chunk, MChunk.hasLength(3))) // true console.log(pipe(chunk, MChunk.hasLength(2))) // false . Signature . export declare const hasLength: (l: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; boolean . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#haslength", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#haslength" },"127": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Utils", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#utils", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#utils" },"128": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "findAll", "content": "Returns a Chunk of the indexes of all elements of self satisfying predicate. | Use to locate every position matching a condition. | Indexes are returned in ascending order. | Returns an empty chunk when no element matches. | . Example (Indexes of matching elements) . import { Chunk, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MChunk from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MChunk\" import * as MPredicate from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MPredicate\" const chunk = Chunk.make(1, 2, 3, 2, 4) console.log(pipe(chunk, MChunk.findAll(MPredicate.strictEquals(2)))) // Chunk(1, 3) . Signature . export declare const findAll: &lt;B extends A, A = B&gt;( predicate: Predicate.Predicate&lt;A&gt; ) =&gt; (self: Type&lt;B&gt;) =&gt; Chunk.Chunk&lt;number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#findall", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#findall" },"129": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "takeBut", "content": "Returns a chunk containing all elements of self except the last n. | Use to drop a suffix of fixed size. | When n &gt;= self.length, returns an empty chunk. | When n &lt;= 0, returns self unchanged. | . Example (Drop trailing elements) . import { Chunk, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MChunk from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MChunk\" const chunk = Chunk.make(1, 2, 3, 4, 5) console.log(pipe(chunk, MChunk.takeBut(2))) // Chunk(1, 2, 3) . Signature . export declare const takeBut: (n: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Chunk.Chunk&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#takebut", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#takebut" },"130": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "takeRightBut", "content": "Returns a chunk containing all elements of self except the first n. | Use to drop a prefix of fixed size. | When n &gt;= self.length, returns an empty chunk. | When n &lt;= 0, returns self unchanged. | . Example (Drop leading elements) . import { Chunk, pipe } from \"effect\" import * as MChunk from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MChunk\" const chunk = Chunk.make(1, 2, 3, 4, 5) console.log(pipe(chunk, MChunk.takeRightBut(2))) // Chunk(3, 4, 5) . Signature . export declare const takeRightBut: (n: number) =&gt; &lt;A&gt;(self: Type&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Chunk.Chunk&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#takerightbut", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html#takerightbut" },"131": { "doc": "Chunk.ts", "title": "Chunk.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Chunk.ts.html" },"132": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Color overview", "content": "This module defines the abstract Color type, the base for all ANSI color kinds (ThreeBit, EightBit, and RGB) . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#color-overview", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#color-overview" },"133": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Destructors . | toString | . | Equivalences . | equivalence | . | Getters . | backgroundId | backgroundSequence | foregroundId | foregroundSequence | . | Models . | Type (class) . | [MData.idSymbol] (method) | foregroundId (property) | backgroundId (property) | foregroundSequence (property) | backgroundSequence (property) | . | . | Module markers . | moduleTag | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html" },"134": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Destructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#destructors", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#destructors" },"135": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "toString", "content": "Gets the id of self . Signature . export declare const toString: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, string&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#tostring", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#tostring" },"136": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Equivalences", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#equivalences", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#equivalences" },"137": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "equivalence", "content": "Equivalence . Signature . export declare const equivalence: Equivalence.Equivalence&lt;Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#equivalence", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#equivalence" },"138": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Getters", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#getters", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#getters" },"139": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "backgroundId", "content": "Gets the background id of self . Signature . export declare const backgroundId: (self: Type) =&gt; string . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#backgroundid", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#backgroundid" },"140": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "backgroundSequence", "content": "Gets the background sequence of self . Signature . export declare const backgroundSequence: (self: Type) =&gt; ASSequence.OverOne . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#backgroundsequence", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#backgroundsequence" },"141": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "foregroundId", "content": "Gets the foreground id of self . Signature . export declare const foregroundId: (self: Type) =&gt; string . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#foregroundid", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#foregroundid" },"142": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "foregroundSequence", "content": "Gets the foreground sequence of self . Signature . export declare const foregroundSequence: (self: Type) =&gt; ASSequence.OverOne . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#foregroundsequence", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#foregroundsequence" },"143": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#models" },"144": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Type (class)", "content": "Color Type . Signature . export declare class Type { constructor({ foregroundId, foregroundSequence }: { readonly foregroundId: string readonly foregroundSequence: ASSequence.OverOne }) } . [MData.idSymbol] (method) . Returns the id of this . Signature . [MData.idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string) . foregroundId (property) . Id of this color used as foreground color . Signature . readonly foregroundId: string . backgroundId (property) . Id of this color used as background color . Signature . readonly backgroundId: string . foregroundSequence (property) . Sequence of this color used as foreground color . Signature . readonly foregroundSequence: ASSequence.OverOne . backgroundSequence (property) . Sequence of this color used as background color . Signature . readonly backgroundSequence: ASSequence.OverOne . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#type-class", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#type-class" },"145": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Module markers", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#module-markers", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#module-markers" },"146": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "moduleTag", "content": "Module tag . Signature . export declare const moduleTag: \"@parischap/ansi-styles/Color/\" . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#moduletag", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html#moduletag" },"147": { "doc": "Color/Color.ts", "title": "Color/Color.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Color/Color.ts.html" },"148": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "ContextStyler overview", "content": "This module implements a type that applies to a string or text a style that depends on a context object. Two constructors are provided: . | makeConstant: creates a ContextStyler that always applies the same style regardless of the context. Useful when a function expects a ContextStyler but should ignore the context. | makePaletteBased: creates a ContextStyler that contains a Palette (an array of styles) and a function that transforms a context object into an index. The style that is applied is the one at position index (modulo the number of styles in the Palette). | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#contextstyler-overview", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#contextstyler-overview" },"149": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constructors . | makeConstant | makePaletteBased | . | Getters . | id | style | . | Instances . | black | blue | cyan | green | magenta | none | red | white | yellow | . | Models . | Any (interface) | Never (interface) | Type (class) . | [MData.idSymbol] (method) | id (property) | style (property) | . | . | Module markers . | moduleTag | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html" },"150": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#constructors" },"151": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "makeConstant", "content": "Constructor of a constant ContextStyler that always applies the same style regardless of the context . Signature . export declare const makeConstant: ({ style }: { readonly style: ASStyle.Type }) =&gt; Type&lt;unknown&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#makeconstant", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#makeconstant" },"152": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "makePaletteBased", "content": "Constructor of a palette-based ContextStyler that selects a style from a palette based on a context object of type C. The indexFromContext function must return an integer index from a value of type C. Use a named function or function declaration for indexFromContext (don’t use an arrow function), otherwise the name of this ContextStyler will be meaningless (e.g. function depth(c) { return c. depth; }, not (c)=&gt;c.depth ). Signature . export declare const makePaletteBased: &lt;C&gt;({ palette, indexFromContext }: { readonly palette: ASPalette.Type readonly indexFromContext: (c: C) =&gt; number }) =&gt; Type&lt;C&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#makepalettebased", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#makepalettebased" },"153": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Getters", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#getters", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#getters" },"154": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "id", "content": "Gets the id of self . Signature . export declare const id: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Any, string&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#id", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#id" },"155": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "style", "content": "Gets the style function of self . Signature . export declare const style: &lt;C&gt;(self: Type&lt;C&gt;) =&gt; Type&lt;C&gt;[\"style\"] . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#style", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#style" },"156": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Instances", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#instances", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#instances" },"157": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "black", "content": "Original black color instance . Signature . export declare const black: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#black", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#black" },"158": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "blue", "content": "Original blue color instance . Signature . export declare const blue: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#blue", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#blue" },"159": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "cyan", "content": "Original cyan color instance . Signature . export declare const cyan: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#cyan", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#cyan" },"160": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "green", "content": "Original green color instance . Signature . export declare const green: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#green", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#green" },"161": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "magenta", "content": "Original magenta color instance . Signature . export declare const magenta: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#magenta", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#magenta" },"162": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "none", "content": "None ASContextStyler instance: does not apply any style . Signature . export declare const none: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#none", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#none" },"163": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "red", "content": "Original red color instance . Signature . export declare const red: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#red", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#red" },"164": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "white", "content": "Original white color instance . Signature . export declare const white: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#white", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#white" },"165": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "yellow", "content": "Original yellow color instance . Signature . export declare const yellow: Never . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#yellow", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#yellow" },"166": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#models" },"167": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Any (interface)", "content": "Type of an ASContextStyler to which any ASContextStyler can be assigned . Signature . export interface Any extends Type&lt;never&gt; {} . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#any-interface", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#any-interface" },"168": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Never (interface)", "content": "Type of an ASContextStyler that can be assigned to any ASContextStyler (i.e an ASContextStyler that works with any context object) . Signature . export interface Never extends Type&lt;unknown&gt; {} . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#never-interface", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#never-interface" },"169": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Type (class)", "content": "Type that represents an ASContextStyler . Signature . export declare class Type&lt;C&gt; { public constructor({ id, style }: MTypes.Data&lt;Type&lt;C&gt;&gt;) } . [MData.idSymbol] (method) . Returns the id of this . Signature . [MData.idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string) . id (property) . Id of this ContextStyler instance. Useful for equality and debugging . Signature . readonly id: string . style (property) . Function that takes a context c and returns an ASStyle . Signature . readonly style: (c: C) =&gt; ASStyle.Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#type-class", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#type-class" },"170": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "Module markers", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#module-markers", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#module-markers" },"171": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "moduleTag", "content": "Module tag . Signature . export declare const moduleTag: \"@parischap/ansi-styles/ContextStyler/\" . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#moduletag", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html#moduletag" },"172": { "doc": "ContextStyler.ts", "title": "ContextStyler.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/ContextStyler.ts.html" },"173": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Data overview", "content": "Base class for inspectable, pipeable data objects. ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#data-overview", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#data-overview" },"174": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Mental model", "content": ". | Class extends Pipeable.Class and implements Inspectable.Inspectable. It is the recommended root class for value objects in Effect-based packages. | Subclasses must implement [idSymbol], returning either a string identifier (used as _id in the JSON view) or a function producing a fully custom string representation. | Class does not implement Equal.Equal; for value-based equality, extend {@link “./EquivalenceBasedEqualityData.js” | MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.Class} instead. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#mental-model", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#mental-model" },"175": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Common tasks", "content": ". | Define a value object: extend {@link Class} and implement {@link idSymbol} | Customize printing: return a function from [idSymbol] | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#common-tasks", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#common-tasks" },"176": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Quickstart", "content": "Example (Defining a value object) . import * as MData from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MData\" class Point extends MData.Class { constructor( readonly x: number, readonly y: number ) { super() } [MData.idSymbol]() { return \"@example/Point/\" } } console.log(new Point(1, 2).toJSON()) // { _id: '@example/Point/', x: 1, y: 2 } . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#quickstart", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#quickstart" },"177": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Model symbols . | idSymbol | . | Models . | Class (class) . | [idSymbol] (method) | toJSON (method) | [Inspectable.NodeInspectSymbol] (method) | toString (method) | . | Type (type alias) | . | Module markers . | moduleTag | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html" },"178": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Model symbols", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#model-symbols", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#model-symbols" },"179": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "idSymbol", "content": "Symbol naming the id method that subclasses implement. | When the method returns a string, toString and toJSON use it as the _id key alongside the own enumerable properties of the instance. | When the method returns a function, toString and toJSON return whatever that function produces, bound to this. | . Signature . export declare const idSymbol: typeof idSymbol . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#idsymbol", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#idsymbol" },"180": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#models" },"181": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Class (class)", "content": "Abstract base class providing Pipeable and Inspectable for value objects. Signature . export declare class Class . [idSymbol] (method) . Returns the id of this. A string identifier is used as the _id field of the JSON view; a function produces a fully custom representation when invoked with this bound. Signature . abstract [idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string); . toJSON (method) . Returns the JSON view of this. Signature . toJSON(): unknown . [Inspectable.NodeInspectSymbol] (method) . Hooks into Node.js util.inspect. Signature . [Inspectable.NodeInspectSymbol](): unknown . toString (method) . Returns the printable representation of this. Signature . override toString(): string . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#class-class", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#class-class" },"182": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Type (type alias)", "content": "Type of objects produced by this module. Signature . export type Type = Pipeable.Pipeable &amp; Inspectable.Inspectable &amp; { [idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string) } . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#type-type-alias", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#type-type-alias" },"183": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Module markers", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#module-markers", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#module-markers" },"184": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "moduleTag", "content": "Module tag. Signature . export declare const moduleTag: \"@parischap/effect-lib/Data/\" . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#moduletag", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html#moduletag" },"185": { "doc": "Data/Data.ts", "title": "Data/Data.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Data/Data.ts.html" },"186": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "DateTime overview", "content": "This module implements an immutable CVDateTime object. CVDateTime objects keep an internal state. But all provided functions are pure insofar as they always yield the same result whatever the state the object is in. The state is only used to improve performance but does not alter the results. Unlike the JavaScript Date objects and the Effect DateTime objects, CVDateTime objects handle both the Gregorian and Iso calendars. So you can easily get/set the iso year and iso week of a CVDateTime object. A CVDateTime object has a zoneOffset which is the difference in hours between the time in the local zone and UTC time (e.g. zoneOffset=1 for timezone +1:00). All the data in a CVDateTime object is zoneOffset-dependent, except timestamp. An important thing to note is that a CVDateTime object with a timestamp t and a zoneOffset zo has exactly the same date parts (year, ordinalDay, month, monthDay, isoYear…) as a CVDateTime object with timestamp = t+zox3600 and zoneOffset = 0. That’s the reason for the zonedTimestamp field which is equal to t+zox3600. All calculations are performed UTC using zonedTimestamp instead of timestamp. ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#datetime-overview", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#datetime-overview" },"187": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constants . | LOCAL_TIME_ZONE_OFFSET | MAX_FULL_YEAR | MAX_TIMESTAMP | MIN_FULL_YEAR | MIN_TIMESTAMP | . | Constructors . | fromDate | fromEffectDateTime | fromParts | fromPartsOrThrow | fromTimestamp | fromTimestampOrThrow | now | . | Destructors . | getHour11 | getHour23 | getIsoString | getIsoWeek | getIsoYear | getMeridiem | getMillisecond | getMinute | getMonth | getMonthDay | getOrdinalDay | getSecond | getWeekday | getYear | getZoneHour | getZoneMinute | getZoneSecond | . | Equivalences . | equivalence | . | Getters . | gregorianDate | isoDate | time | timestamp | zoneOffsetParts | . | Models . | Type (class) . | uncalculatedFromTimestamp (static method) | uncalculatedFromZonedTimestamp (static method) | fromTimestamp (static method) | now (static method) | fromParts (static method) | [MData.idSymbol] (method) | _setTimestamp (method) | _setZoneOffset (method) | _setGregorianDate (method) | _setIsoDate (method) | _setTime (method) | [Hash.symbol] (method) | [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.isEquivalentToSymbol] (method) | [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.hasSameTypeMarkerAsSymbol] (method) | timestamp (property) | zoneOffset (property) | zonedTimestamp (property) | . | . | Module markers . | moduleTag | . | Offsetters . | offsetDays | offsetDaysOrThrow | offsetHours | offsetHoursOrThrow | offsetIsoYears | offsetIsoYearsOrThrow | offsetMilliseconds | offsetMillisecondsOrThrow | offsetMinutes | offsetMinutesOrThrow | offsetMonths | offsetMonthsOrThrow | offsetSeconds | offsetSecondsOrThrow | offsetYears | offsetYearsOrThrow | toFirstIsoYearDay | toFirstMonthDay | toFirstYearDay | toLastIsoYearDay | toLastIsoYearWeek | toLastMonthDay | toLastYearDay | . | Predicates . | isFirstIsoYearDay | isFirstMonthDay | isFirstYearDay | isLastIsoYearDay | isLastMonthDay | isLastYearDay | isoYearIsLong | yearIsLeap | . | Setters . | setHour11 | setHour11OrThrow | setHour23 | setHour23OrThrow | setIsoWeek | setIsoWeekOrThrow | setIsoYear | setIsoYearOrThrow | setMeridiem | setMillisecond | setMillisecondOrThrow | setMinute | setMinuteOrThrow | setMonth | setMonthDay | setMonthDayOrThrow | setMonthOrThrow | setOrdinalDay | setOrdinalDayOrThrow | setSecond | setSecondOrThrow | setWeekday | setWeekdayOrThrow | setYear | setYearOrThrow | setZoneOffsetKeepParts | setZoneOffsetKeepPartsOrThrow | setZoneOffsetKeepTimestamp | setZoneOffsetKeepTimestampOrThrow | . | Utils . | toDate | toEffectDateTime | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html" },"188": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Constants", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#constants", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#constants" },"189": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "LOCAL_TIME_ZONE_OFFSET", "content": "Local time zone offset in hours of the machine on which this code runs. The value is calculated once at startup. Signature . export declare const LOCAL_TIME_ZONE_OFFSET: number . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#local_time_zone_offset", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#local_time_zone_offset" },"190": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "MAX_FULL_YEAR", "content": "Maximal usable year (ECMA-262) . Signature . export declare const MAX_FULL_YEAR: number . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#max_full_year", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#max_full_year" },"191": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "MAX_TIMESTAMP", "content": "Maximal usable timestamp (ECMA-262) . Signature . export declare const MAX_TIMESTAMP: 8640000000000000 . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#max_timestamp", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#max_timestamp" },"192": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "MIN_FULL_YEAR", "content": "Minimal usable year (ECMA-262) . Signature . export declare const MIN_FULL_YEAR: number . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#min_full_year", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#min_full_year" },"193": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "MIN_TIMESTAMP", "content": "Minimal usable timestamp (ECMA-262) . Signature . export declare const MIN_TIMESTAMP: number . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#min_timestamp", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#min_timestamp" },"194": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#constructors" },"195": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "fromDate", "content": "Builds a CVDateTime from a Javascript Date . Signature . export declare const fromDate: (date: Date) =&gt; Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromdate", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromdate" },"196": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "fromEffectDateTime", "content": "Builds a CVDateTime from an Effect.DateTime.Zoned . Signature . export declare const fromEffectDateTime: (date: DateTime.Zoned) =&gt; Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromeffectdatetime", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromeffectdatetime" },"197": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "fromParts", "content": "Tries to build a CVDateTime from the provided parts. Returns a Success if successful, a Failure otherwise. year must comprised in the range [MIN_FULL_YEAR, MAX_FULL_YEAR]. ordinalDay must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the number of days in the current year. month must be greater than or equal to 1 (January) and less than or equal to 12 (December). monthDay must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the number of days in the current month. isoYear must be comprised in the range [MIN_FULL_YEAR, MAX_FULL_YEAR]. isoWeek must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the number of iso weeks in the current year. weekday must be greater than or equal to 1 (monday) and less than or equal to 7 (sunday). If there is not sufficient information to determine the exact day of the year, i.e. none of the three following tuples is fully determined [year, ordinalDay], [year, month, monthDay], [isoYear, isoWeek, weekday], default values are determined in the following order (the first match stops the process): . | If year and month are set, monthDay is taken equal to 1. | If year and monthDay are set, month is taken equal to 1. | If year is set and both month and monthDay are undefined, the day is taken to be the first one in the year. | If isoYear and isoWeek are set, weekday is taken equal to 1. | If isoYear and weekday are set, isoWeek is taken equal to 1. | If isoYear is set and both isoWeek and weekday are undefined, the day is taken to be the first one in the iso year. | If both year and isoYear are undefined, an error is raised. | . hour23 must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 23. hour11 must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 11. meridiem must be one of 0 (AM) or 12 (PM). If there is not sufficient information to determine the hour of the day, i.e. none of the two following tuples is fully determined [hour23], [hour11, meridiem], default values are determined as follows: . | If meridiem is set, hour11 is taken equal to 0. | If hour11 is set, meridiem is taken equal to 0. | Otherwise, meridiem and hour11 are taken equal to 0. | . minute must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. If omitted, minute is assumed to be 0. second must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. If omitted, second is assumed to be 0. millisecond must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 999. If omitted, millisecond is assumed to be 0. zoneOffset must be strictly greater than -13 and strictly less than 15. zoneHour must be greater than or equal to -12 and less than or equal to 14. zoneMinute must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. zoneSecond must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. If there is not sufficient information to determine the exact time zone offset, i.e. none of the two following tuples is fully determined [zoneOffset], [zoneHour, zoneMinute, zoneSecond], default values are determined as follows : . | If all parameters are undefined, the local time zone offset of the machine this code is running on is used. ATTENTION: unlike the JavaScript Date constructor, fromParts uses the current time zone offset, not the one that prevails at the given date (so, in Paris, in winter, the time zone offset for date 20250714 is -1 and not -2). | If any of zoneHour, zoneMinute, zoneSecond is defined, the remaining undefined parameters are taken equal to 0. | . Note that zoneHour=-0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0 is different from zoneHour=0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0. The first corresponds to the string ‘GMT-00:10’, a negative 10-minute offset, the second one to the string ‘GMT+00:10’, a positive 10-minute offset. year, ordinalDay, month, monthDay, isoYear, isoWeek, weekday, hour23, hour11, minute, second, millisecond, zoneHour, zoneMinute and zoneSecond should be integers. zoneOffset does not need to be an integer. All parameters must be coherent. For instance, year=1970, month=1, monthDay=1, weekday=0 zoneHour=0, zoneMinute=0 and zoneSecond=0 will trigger an error because 1/1/1970 00:00:00:000+0:00 is a thursday. hour23=13 and meridiem=0 will also trigger an error. Signature . export declare const fromParts: (params: CVDateTimeParts.Type) =&gt; Result.Result&lt;Type, MInputError.Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromparts", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromparts" },"198": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "fromPartsOrThrow", "content": "Same as fromParts but returns directly a CVDateTime or throws if it cannot be built . Signature . export declare const fromPartsOrThrow: (parts: CVDateTimeParts.Type) =&gt; Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#frompartsorthrow", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#frompartsorthrow" },"199": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "fromTimestamp", "content": "Tries to build a CVDateTime from timestamp, the number of milliseconds since 1/1/1970 00:00:00:000+0:00, and zoneOffset which gives the offset between the local time and the UTC time. Returns a Success if successful, a Failure otherwise. timestamp must be greater than or equal to MIN_TIMESTAMP and less than or equal to MAX_TIMESTAMP. If zoneOffset is omitted, the local time zone offset of the machine this code is running on is used. zoneOffset can be expressed as a number of hours. In this case, it must be strictly greater to . | 13 and strictly less than 15. | . It can also be expressed as an object containing three components: . | zoneHour which must be greater than or equal to -12 and less than or equal to 14. | zoneMinute which must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. | zoneSecond which must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. | . Note that zoneHour=-0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0 is different from zoneHour=0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0. The first corresponds to the string ‘GMT-00:10’, a negative 10-minute offset, the second one to the string ‘GMT+00:10’, a positive 10-minute offset. timestamp, zoneHour, zoneMinute and zoneSecond should be integers. zoneOffset, when expressed as a number of hours, does not need to be an integer. Signature . export declare const fromTimestamp: ( timestamp: number, zoneOffset?: number | { readonly zoneHour: number; readonly zoneMinute: number; readonly zoneSecond: number } ) =&gt; Result.Result&lt;Type, MInputError.Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromtimestamp", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromtimestamp" },"200": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "fromTimestampOrThrow", "content": "Same as fromTimestamp but returns directly a CVDateTime or throws if it cannot be built . Signature . export declare const fromTimestampOrThrow: ( timestamp: number, zoneOffset?: number | { readonly zoneHour: number; readonly zoneMinute: number; readonly zoneSecond: number } ) =&gt; Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromtimestamporthrow", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#fromtimestamporthrow" },"201": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "now", "content": "Builds a CVDateTime using Date.now() as timestamp. zoneOffset is set to 0. Signature . export declare const now: () =&gt; Type . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#now", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#now" },"202": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Destructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#destructors", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#destructors" },"203": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getHour11", "content": "Returns the hour11 of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getHour11: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#gethour11", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#gethour11" },"204": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getHour23", "content": "Returns the hour23 of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getHour23: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#gethour23", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#gethour23" },"205": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getIsoString", "content": "Returns the ISO representation of this DateTime . Signature . export declare const getIsoString: (self: Type) =&gt; string . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getisostring", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getisostring" },"206": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getIsoWeek", "content": "Returns the isoWeek of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getIsoWeek: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getisoweek", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getisoweek" },"207": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getIsoYear", "content": "Returns the isoYear of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getIsoYear: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getisoyear", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getisoyear" },"208": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getMeridiem", "content": "Returns the meridiem of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getMeridiem: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, 0 | 12&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmeridiem", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmeridiem" },"209": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getMillisecond", "content": "Returns the millisecond of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getMillisecond: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmillisecond", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmillisecond" },"210": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getMinute", "content": "Returns the minute of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getMinute: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getminute", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getminute" },"211": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getMonth", "content": "Returns the month of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getMonth: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmonth", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmonth" },"212": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getMonthDay", "content": "Returns the monthDay of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getMonthDay: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmonthday", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getmonthday" },"213": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getOrdinalDay", "content": "Returns the ordinalDay of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getOrdinalDay: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getordinalday", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getordinalday" },"214": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getSecond", "content": "Returns the second of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getSecond: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getsecond", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getsecond" },"215": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getWeekday", "content": "Returns the weekday of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getWeekday: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getweekday", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getweekday" },"216": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getYear", "content": "Returns the (Gregorian) year of self for the given time zone . Signature . export declare const getYear: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getyear", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getyear" },"217": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getZoneHour", "content": "Returns the hour part of the zoneOffset of self . Signature . export declare const getZoneHour: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getzonehour", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getzonehour" },"218": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getZoneMinute", "content": "Returns the minute part of the zoneOffset of self . Signature . export declare const getZoneMinute: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getzoneminute", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getzoneminute" },"219": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "getZoneSecond", "content": "Returns the second part of the zoneOffset of self . Signature . export declare const getZoneSecond: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getzonesecond", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getzonesecond" },"220": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Equivalences", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#equivalences", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#equivalences" },"221": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "equivalence", "content": "Equivalence . Signature . export declare const equivalence: Equivalence.Equivalence&lt;Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#equivalence", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#equivalence" },"222": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Getters", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getters", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#getters" },"223": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "gregorianDate", "content": "Returns the gregorianDate property of self . Signature . export declare const gregorianDate: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, CVGregorianDate.Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#gregoriandate", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#gregoriandate" },"224": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "isoDate", "content": "Returns the isoDate property of self . Signature . export declare const isoDate: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, CVIsoDate.Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#isodate", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#isodate" },"225": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "time", "content": "Returns the time property of self . Signature . export declare const time: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, CVTime.Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#time", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#time" },"226": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "timestamp", "content": "Returns the timestamp property of self as a number . Signature . export declare const timestamp: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, number&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#timestamp", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#timestamp" },"227": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "zoneOffsetParts", "content": "Returns the zoneOffsetParts property of self . Signature . export declare const zoneOffsetParts: MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, CVZoneOffsetParts.Type&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#zoneoffsetparts", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#zoneoffsetparts" },"228": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#models" },"229": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Type (class)", "content": "Type that represents a CVDateTime . Signature . export declare class Type { private constructor({ timestamp, _gregorianDate, _isoDate, _time, zoneOffset, _zoneOffsetParts, zonedTimestamp }: { readonly timestamp: number readonly _gregorianDate: Option.Option&lt;CVGregorianDate.Type&gt; readonly _isoDate: Option.Option&lt;CVIsoDate.Type&gt; readonly _time: Option.Option&lt;CVTime.Type&gt; readonly zoneOffset: number readonly _zoneOffsetParts: Option.Option&lt;CVZoneOffsetParts.Type&gt; readonly zonedTimestamp: number }) } . uncalculatedFromTimestamp (static method) . Constructor that creates a DateTime from a timestamp and a zoneOffset for which no calculations have been carried out yet. The zonedTimestamp field is automatically calculated. Does not check any input parameters . Signature . private static uncalculatedFromTimestamp(timestamp: number, zoneOffset: number): Type . uncalculatedFromZonedTimestamp (static method) . Constructor that creates a DateTime from a zonedTimestamp and a zoneOffset for which no calculations have been carried out yet. The timestamp field is automatically calculated. Does not check any input parameters . Signature . private static uncalculatedFromZonedTimestamp(zonedTimestamp: number, zoneOffset: number): Type . fromTimestamp (static method) . Tries to build a CVDateTime from timestamp, the number of milliseconds since 1/1/1970 00:00:00:000+0:00, and zoneOffset which gives the offset between the local time and the UTC time. Returns a Success if successful, a Failure otherwise. timestamp must be greater than or equal to MIN_TIMESTAMP and less than or equal to MAX_TIMESTAMP. If zoneOffset is omitted, the local time zone offset of the machine this code is running on is used. zoneOffset can be expressed as a number of hours. In this case, it must be strictly greater to . | 13 and strictly less than 15. | . It can also be expressed as an object containing three components: . | zoneHour which must be greater than or equal to -12 and less than or equal to 14. | zoneMinute which must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. | zoneSecond which must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. | . Note that zoneHour=-0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0 is different from zoneHour=0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0. The first corresponds to the string ‘GMT-00:10’, a negative 10-minute offset, the second one to the string ‘GMT+00:10’, a positive 10-minute offset. timestamp, zoneHour, zoneMinute and zoneSecond should be integers. zoneOffset, when expressed as a number of hours, does not need to be an integer. Signature . static fromTimestamp( timestamp: number, zoneOffset?: | number | { readonly zoneHour: number; readonly zoneMinute: number; readonly zoneSecond: number; }, ): Result.Result&lt;Type, MInputError.Type&gt; . now (static method) . Builds a CVDateTime using Date.now() as timestamp. zoneOffset is set to 0. Signature . static now(): Type . fromParts (static method) . Tries to build a CVDateTime from the provided parts. Returns a Success if successful, a Failure otherwise. year must comprised in the range [MIN_FULL_YEAR, MAX_FULL_YEAR]. ordinalDay must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the number of days in the current year. month must be greater than or equal to 1 (January) and less than or equal to 12 (December). monthDay must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the number of days in the current month. isoYear must be comprised in the range [MIN_FULL_YEAR, MAX_FULL_YEAR]. isoWeek must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the number of iso weeks in the current year. weekday must be greater than or equal to 1 (monday) and less than or equal to 7 (sunday). If there is not sufficient information to determine the exact day of the year, i.e. none of the three following tuples is fully determined [year, ordinalDay], [year, month, monthDay], [isoYear, isoWeek, weekday], default values are determined in the following order (the first match stops the process): . | If year and month are set, monthDay is taken equal to 1. | If year and monthDay are set, month is taken equal to 1. | If year is set and both month and monthDay are undefined, the day is taken to be the first one in the year. | If isoYear and isoWeek are set, weekday is taken equal to 1. | If isoYear and weekday are set, isoWeek is taken equal to 1. | If isoYear is set and both isoWeek and weekday are undefined, the day is taken to be the first one in the iso year. | If both year and isoYear are undefined, an error is raised. | . hour23 must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 23. hour11 must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 11. meridiem must be one of 0 (AM) or 12 (PM). If there is not sufficient information to determine the hour of the day, i.e. none of the two following tuples is fully determined [hour23], [hour11, meridiem], default values are determined as follows: . | If meridiem is set, hour11 is taken equal to 0. | If hour11 is set, meridiem is taken equal to 0. | Otherwise, meridiem and hour11 are taken equal to 0. | . minute must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. If omitted, minute is assumed to be 0. second must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. If omitted, second is assumed to be 0. millisecond must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 999. If omitted, millisecond is assumed to be 0. zoneOffset must be strictly greater than -13 and strictly less than 15. zoneHour must be greater than or equal to -12 and less than or equal to 14. zoneMinute must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. zoneSecond must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59. If there is not sufficient information to determine the exact time zone offset, i.e. none of the two following tuples is fully determined [zoneOffset], [zoneHour, zoneMinute, zoneSecond], default values are determined as follows : . | If all parameters are undefined, the local time zone offset of the machine this code is running on is used. ATTENTION: unlike the JavaScript Date constructor, fromParts uses the current time zone offset, not the one that prevails at the given date (so, in Paris, in winter, the time zone offset for date 20250714 is -1 and not -2). | If any of zoneHour, zoneMinute, zoneSecond is defined, the remaining undefined parameters are taken equal to 0. | . Note that zoneHour=-0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0 is different from zoneHour=0, zoneMinute=10, zoneSecond=0. The first corresponds to the string ‘GMT-00:10’, a negative 10-minute offset, the second one to the string ‘GMT+00:10’, a positive 10-minute offset. year, ordinalDay, month, monthDay, isoYear, isoWeek, weekday, hour23, hour11, minute, second, millisecond, zoneHour, zoneMinute and zoneSecond should be integers. zoneOffset does not need to be an integer. All parameters must be coherent. For instance, year=1970, month=1, monthDay=1, weekday=0 zoneHour=0, zoneMinute=0 and zoneSecond=0 will trigger an error because 1/1/1970 00:00:00:000+0:00 is a thursday. hour23=13 and meridiem=0 will also trigger an error. Signature . static fromParts({ year, ordinalDay, month, monthDay, isoYear, isoWeek, weekday, hour23, hour11, meridiem, minute, second, millisecond, zoneOffset, zoneHour, zoneMinute, zoneSecond, }: CVDateTimeParts.Type): Result.Result&lt;Type, MInputError.Type&gt; . [MData.idSymbol] (method) . Returns the id of this . Signature . [MData.idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string) . _setTimestamp (method) . If possible, returns a Success of a copy of self with timestamp set to timestamp. Returns a Failure of an error otherwise. timestamp must be an integer comprised in the range [MIN_TIMESTAMP, MAX_TIMESTAMP] representing the number of milliseconds since 1/1/1970 00:00:00:000+0:00. Signature . _setTimestamp(timestamp: number): Result.Result&lt;Type, MInputError.Type&gt; . _setZoneOffset (method) . If possible, returns a Success of a copy of self with zoneOffset set to zoneOffset. Returns a Failure of an error otherwise. timestamp must be an integer comprised in the range [MIN_TIMESTAMP, MAX_TIMESTAMP] representing the number of milliseconds since 1/1/1970 00:00:00:000+0:00. Signature . _setZoneOffset( keepTimestamp: boolean, zoneOffset: | number | { readonly zoneHour: number; readonly zoneMinute: number; readonly zoneSecond: number; } = LOCAL_TIME_ZONE_OFFSET, ): Result.Result&lt;Type, MInputError.Type&gt; . _setGregorianDate (method) . Returns a copy of this with _gregorianDate set to gregorianDate . Signature . _setGregorianDate(gregorianDate: CVGregorianDate.Type): Type . _setIsoDate (method) . Returns a copy of this with isoDate set to isoDate . Signature . _setIsoDate(isoDate: CVIsoDate.Type): Type . _setTime (method) . Returns a copy of this with time set to time . Signature . _setTime(time: CVTime.Type): Type . [Hash.symbol] (method) . Calculates the hash value of this . Signature . [Hash.symbol](): number . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.isEquivalentToSymbol] (method) . Function that implements the equivalence of this and that . Signature . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.isEquivalentToSymbol](this: this, that: this): boolean . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.hasSameTypeMarkerAsSymbol] (method) . Predicate that returns true if that has the same type marker as this . Signature . [MEquivalenceBasedEqualityData.hasSameTypeMarkerAsSymbol](that: unknown): boolean . timestamp (property) . Timestamp of this DateTime (timezone-independent) . Signature . readonly timestamp: number . zoneOffset (property) . Offset in hours between the time of the zone for which all calculations of that DateTime object will be carried out and UTC time (e.g zoneOffset=1 for timezone +1:00). Not necessarily an integer, range: ]-13, 15[ . Signature . readonly zoneOffset: number . zonedTimestamp (property) . Calculated field equal to timestamp + zoneOffsetx3600 . Signature . readonly zonedTimestamp: number . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#type-class", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#type-class" },"230": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Module markers", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#module-markers", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#module-markers" },"231": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "moduleTag", "content": "Module tag . Signature . export declare const moduleTag: \"@parischap/conversions/DateTime/\" . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#moduletag", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#moduletag" },"232": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "Offsetters", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#offsetters", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#offsetters" },"233": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "offsetDays", "content": "If possible, returns a Success of a copy of self offset by offset days. Returns a Failure of an error otherwise. Signature . export declare const offsetDays: (offset: number) =&gt; MTypes.OneArgFunction&lt;Type, Result.Result&lt;Type, MInputError.Type&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#offsetdays", "relUrl": "/conversions/DateTime/DateTime.ts.html#offsetdays" },"234": { "doc": "DateTime/DateTime.ts", "title": "offsetDaysOrThrow", "content": "Same as offsetDays but returns directly a CVDateTime or throws in case of an error . Signature . exp