 number&gt;&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#parseasnumberorthrow", "relUrl": "/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#parseasnumberorthrow" },"953": { "doc": "formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#models" },"954": { "doc": "formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts", "title": "Type (class)", "content": "Type that represents a CVNumberBase10Parser . Signature . export declare class Type { constructor(numberFormat: CVNumberBase10Format.Type) } . [MData.idSymbol] (method) . Returns the id of this . Signature . [MData.idSymbol](): string | (() =&gt; string) . description (property) . Description of this parser, e.g. ‘signed integer parser . Signature . readonly description: string . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#type-class", "relUrl": "/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#type-class" },"955": { "doc": "formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts", "title": "Module markers", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#module-markers", "relUrl": "/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#module-markers" },"956": { "doc": "formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts", "title": "moduleTag", "content": "Module tag . Signature . export declare const moduleTag: \"@parischap/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser/\" . ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#moduletag", "relUrl": "/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html#moduletag" },"957": { "doc": "formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts", "title": "formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html", "relUrl": "/conversions/formatting/NumberBase10Format/NumberBase10Parser.ts.html" },"958": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Option overview", "content": "Extension to the Effect Option module providing interoperability with nullable values, JavaScript iterators, and Effect. ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#option-overview", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#option-overview" },"959": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Mental model", "content": ". | Option.Option&lt;A&gt; is a sum of Some&lt;A&gt; and None. | This module focuses on bridging Option with non-Effect-aware shapes (nullable values, raw iterators) and lifting it into Effect. | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#mental-model", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#mental-model" },"960": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Common tasks", "content": ". | Bridge with nullables: {@link OptionOrNullable}, {@link fromOptionOrNullable} | Bridge with iterators: {@link fromNextIteratorValue} | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#common-tasks", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#common-tasks" },"961": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Quickstart", "content": "Example (Bridging from nullable input) . import * as MOption from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MOption\" console.log(MOption.fromOptionOrNullable(null)) // None console.log(MOption.fromOptionOrNullable(undefined)) // None console.log(MOption.fromOptionOrNullable(42)) // Some(42) . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#quickstart", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#quickstart" },"962": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Models . | OptionOrNullable (type alias) | Type (type alias) | . | Utils . | fromNextIteratorValue | fromOptionOrNullable | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html" },"963": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Models", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#models", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#models" },"964": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "OptionOrNullable (type alias)", "content": "Tagged union representing “an optional A” using whichever shape callers find natural: an Option&lt;A&gt;, a bare A, or null/undefined. | Use at API boundaries that accept input from code unaware of Option. | . Signature . export type OptionOrNullable&lt;A&gt; = Option.Option&lt;A&gt; | null | undefined | A . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#optionornullable-type-alias", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#optionornullable-type-alias" },"965": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Type (type alias)", "content": "Type on which this module’s functions operate. Signature . export type Type&lt;A&gt; = Option.Option&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#type-type-alias", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#type-type-alias" },"966": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Utils", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#utils", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#utils" },"967": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "fromNextIteratorValue", "content": "Advances iterator by one step and lifts the result into an Option. | Returns Option.some(value) when the iterator produced a value, Option.none when it is exhausted. | . Example (Pull next value from an iterator) . import * as MOption from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MOption\" const it = [1, 2][Symbol.iterator]() console.log(MOption.fromNextIteratorValue(it)) // Some(1) console.log(MOption.fromNextIteratorValue(it)) // Some(2) console.log(MOption.fromNextIteratorValue(it)) // None . Signature . export declare const fromNextIteratorValue: &lt;A&gt;(iterator: Iterator&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#fromnextiteratorvalue", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#fromnextiteratorvalue" },"968": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "fromOptionOrNullable", "content": "Normalizes an {@link OptionOrNullable} to an Option. | When the input is already an Option, it is returned as-is. | null and undefined become Option.none; any other value becomes Option.some. | . Example (Normalize varied inputs) . import { Option } from \"effect\" import * as MOption from \"@parischap/effect-lib/MOption\" console.log(MOption.fromOptionOrNullable(null)) // None console.log(MOption.fromOptionOrNullable(undefined)) // None console.log(MOption.fromOptionOrNullable(42)) // Some(42) console.log(MOption.fromOptionOrNullable(Option.some(7))) // Some(7) . Signature . export declare const fromOptionOrNullable: &lt;A&gt;(a: OptionOrNullable&lt;A&gt;) =&gt; Option.Option&lt;A&gt; . ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#fromoptionornullable", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html#fromoptionornullable" },"969": { "doc": "Option.ts", "title": "Option.ts", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/effect-lib/Option.ts.html", "relUrl": "/effect-lib/Option.ts.html" },"970": { "doc": "Palette.ts", "title": "Palette overview", "content": "This module defines a Palette, a named collection of Styles used to build PaletteContextStylers . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Palette.ts.html#palette-overview", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Palette.ts.html#palette-overview" },"971": { "doc": "Palette.ts", "title": "Table of contents", "content": ". | Constructors . | make | . | Destructors . | toString | . | Getters . | styles | . | Instances . | allBrightOriginalColors | allOriginalColors | allStandardOriginalColors | . | Models . | Type (class) . | make (static method) | [MData.idSymbol] (method) | styles (property) | . | . | Module markers . | moduleTag | . | Utils . | append | . | . ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Palette.ts.html", "relUrl": "/ansi-styles/Palette.ts.html" },"972": { "doc": "Palette.ts", "title": "Constructors", "content": " ", "url": "/0.1.0/ansi-styles/Palette.ts.html#constructors", "relUrl": "/ans